ole, the implications for the West and the rebalancing of relations between China and its neighbours.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 4aPolitical Studies 2020. 4amanchesterhive variable pricing textbooks. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Comparative Politics.2bisacsh  aChina's foreign policy.  aChinese Communist Party.  aChinese model.  aChinese political system.  aLeninist party-state.  aNational People's Representatives Congress.  aPeople's Republic of China.  aState Council.  acentre-local relations.  adeliberative democracy.1 aCollins, Neil, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCottey, Andrew, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aCottey, Andrew, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 1986 - 2013 eBook Packagez9783111283630oZDB-23-MUP40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781526129796423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781526129796/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-MUPc1986d2013